      "content": "It's natural to feel exhausted and question the value of our efforts when faced with the vastness of the universe and the inevitability of death. But finding purpose and meaning in our struggles doesn't necessarily contradict accepting the reality of our existence. It's about finding a way to live with that reality in a way that brings us peace and fulfillment. The pressure to keep going might feel overwhelming, but it can also be a source of strength and resilience. Embracing our struggles and finding meaning in them can be a way to cope with the nothingness, rather than simply accepting it passively. It's about finding a balance between acknowledging the reality and still striving to make the most of our existence.",
      "source": "target",
